        <section class="project-summary">
            <img src="../images/projects/shell-shock/stills/shell-shock-1.png" alt="Scene from Shell Shock" class="inline-image">
            
            <p>Shell Shock follows the story of Grock, a once-celebrated snail racer whose career was cut short by a mysterious accident. Now living in self-imposed exile in a decaying mansion filled with terrariums, he obsessively breeds racing snails while plotting his comeback. His carefully maintained world is disrupted when his estranged sister Mira, a rising star in the sport, arrives seeking his help.</p>

            <img src="../images/projects/shell-shock/stills/shell-shock-27.png" alt="Scene from Shell Shock" class="large-image">

            <p>As their uneasy reunion unfolds, we discover that both siblings have undergone radical body modifications—a common practice in their world where humans alter themselves to better understand and bond with the creatures they admire. Grock's modifications have progressed to an unsettling degree, while Mira maintains a more socially acceptable balance between human and snail characteristics.</p>

            <img src="../images/projects/shell-shock/stills/shell-shock-21.png" alt="Scene from Shell Shock" class="inline-image left">

            <p>The story explores themes of obsession, sibling rivalry, and the blurred lines between dedication and madness. Set in a world where the sport of snail racing has evolved into a decadent spectacle, the film blends body horror with dark comedy, creating a unique atmosphere that is both unsettling and absurdly humorous.</p>

            <img src="../images/projects/shell-shock/stills/shell-shock-12.png" alt="Scene from Shell Shock" class="inline-image">

            <p>Through a series of flashbacks, we learn about the siblings' complicated past and the incident that led to Grock's withdrawal from the racing world. As Mira's true motives for seeking out her brother become clear, tensions escalate, leading to a climactic race that will determine both their fates.</p>

            <img src="../images/projects/shell-shock/stills/shell-shock-8.png" alt="Scene from Shell Shock" class="inline-image left">

            <p>The film's visual style draws inspiration from Victorian naturalist illustrations, body horror cinema, and the ornate aesthetics of baroque architecture. The mansion's interior, with its countless terrariums and overgrown gardens, creates a greenhouse-like atmosphere where the line between the natural and artificial world becomes increasingly indistinct.</p>

            <img src="../images/projects/shell-shock/stills/shell-shock-16.png" alt="Scene from Shell Shock" class="inline-image">

            <p>Shell Shock examines the lengths people will go to pursue their passions, the price of perfectionism, and the complex dynamics of family relationships. Through its surreal lens, the film poses questions about identity, transformation, and the sometimes razor-thin line between dedication and obsession.</p>
        </section>

